// Semantic direction:
// komprimering reduces data size using statistical and structural redundancy.
// lz4_algoritme prioritizes speed: O(n) compression using a hash_tabell for 4-byte match lookup.
// lz4_sekvens encodes runs as (literal_length, match_offset, match_length) tuples via lz4_token.
// lz4_hc uses a hash_kjede for better match searching at higher lz4_hc_nivå at reduced speed.
// lazy_matching considers the next byte before committing to a match for better compression.
// zstd_fse_koding (Finite State Entropy) is an ANS-based entropy coder replacing Huffman in Zstd.
// fse_normalisér converts symbol frequencies to table entries with bounded error.
// zstd_ordbøker allow pre-training on domain-specific data for much better compression of small inputs.
// brotli_ordbøker_statiske embed ~122KB of pre-defined strings for excellent web content compression.
// brotli_transformasjoner apply case/suffix transforms to dictionary entries for even better matching.
// kanonisk_huffman encodes trees compactly by specifying only code lengths, not the actual codes.
// ans_koding (Asymmetric Numeral Systems) achieves near-entropy coding with O(1) encode/decode.
// asymmetrisk_tallsystem maps symbols to integer state transitions for sub-bit precision.
// multi_tråd_komprimering divides input into parallell_blokk for concurrent encoding.

// Primitive flow:
// lz4 komprimér: hash 4 bytes ved posisjon i -> finn match i hash_tabell
//   match funnet og match_lengde >= 4: emit lz4_sekvens(lit_run, offset, match_len)
//   ingen match: emit literal_lz77 -> fremskritt 1 byte
// zstd komprimér: finn sekvenser (via LDPC-søk) -> samle i sekvens_lagring
//   huffman_tre for literals -> fse for offsets/lengder
//   kode alt til bitstrøm -> zstd_rammer wrapper
// huffman_tre_bygg: tell frekvenser -> prioritetskø
//   trekk to laveste -> slå sammen -> ny node -> gjenta til ett tre
//   tilordne koder: venstre=0, høyre=1 -> kanonisk_huffman sorter etter lengde
// fse: normaliser frekvenser til summa N (potens av 2)
//   bygg state_tabell -> kode symbol via state_overgang

// This defines compression algorithms: LZ4 with hash chain, Zstandard with FSE entropy
// coding and pre-trained dictionaries, Brotli with static dictionaries and transformations,
// canonical Huffman coding, and ANS/FSE arithmetic coding.
